Concerning some abbreviations...

1.) What does `afk' mean?  Here are some common abbreviations:

pk - Player kill
pvp - Player vs Player
wiz - A term often used to refer to immortals
afk - away from keyboard
brb - be right back
brt - be right there

OOC - Out of character.
   Lines are considered OOC. Line usage is covered in <help line use>.

IC - In character.
   Knowledge your character knows. You may know who Vecna is from reading the latest book about him, but your character does not.

OOG - Out of game.
  Stuff that is best left outside of Sundering Shadows. Please do try. This includes a real life friend, real life girlfriends, bosses, the bully from your 12th grade class who picked on you.

IG - In Game.
  The gameworld of Sundering Shadows, with all the dieties, and diverse personalities that we have come up with.
